Citations
Date: 0/0/1981
Source: Loughnan Glossary
Author: LOUGHNAN
Vol / Page: 18
Edition:
Quote: clap: a dog is made to clap - or may do so naturally - when during a run he stops but does not just stand still on his feet or sit on his haunches, but crouches down on his belly.
Notes:

Date: 15/9/1983
Source: NZ Journal of Agriculture
Author:
Vol / Page: 9
Edition:
Quote: Clap - a dog that whenever it's stationary - when working up to sheep - lies flat on the ground, but is still firmly giving them the eye. [clapping (verbal noun)]
